WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:07.128
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: So,

00:02:07.128 --> 00:02:09.152
let's begin now.
First of all,

00:02:09.152 --> 00:02:12.622
I'm assuming all of you have
some idea what special

00:02:12.622 --> 00:02:14.962
relativity means.
There are two theories of

00:02:14.962 --> 00:02:17.209
relativity, one is the special
theory and one is the general

00:02:17.209 --> 00:02:19.420
theory.
The general theory is something

00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:22.574
that we won't do in any detail.
Special theory is something we

00:02:22.574 --> 00:02:26.224
will do in reasonable detail.
So, it's good to begin by

00:02:26.224 --> 00:02:31.948
asking some of you what is your
present understanding of what

00:02:31.948 --> 00:02:35.440
the subject is all about.
Yes, sir?

00:02:35.440 --> 00:02:37.780
The Yale cap,
what do you think it's about?

00:02:37.780 --> 00:02:42.944
Student: It's about
relative speed in two reference

00:02:42.944 --> 00:02:44.557
systems.
Professor Ramamurti

00:02:44.557 --> 00:02:46.036
Shankar: Okay,
it's about relative speed in

00:02:46.036 --> 00:02:47.750
two reference systems.
I'll come to you;

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:51.007
then I'll come to you.
Student: It's based on

00:02:51.007 --> 00:02:55.250
the postulate that the laws of
physics are the same in any two

00:02:55.250 --> 00:02:59.285
references moving in uniform
motion relative to one another

00:02:59.285 --> 00:03:03.319
and the speed of light is
constant in all references.

00:03:03.319 --> 00:03:04.618
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Okay,

00:03:04.618 --> 00:03:07.642
I will take the last row there.
Student: [inaudible]

00:03:07.642 --> 00:03:10.536
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Okay,

00:03:10.536 --> 00:03:14.875
so what I've heard so far is
that the laws of physics are the

00:03:14.875 --> 00:03:19.432
same for two people who are both
in inertial frames of reference

00:03:19.432 --> 00:03:22.760
and the velocity of light's a
constant.

00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:26.506
Right.
That's certainly the way we

00:03:26.506 --> 00:03:28.570
understand the special
relativity theory.

00:03:28.570 --> 00:03:32.146
But it's a very old one.
It's been going on long before

00:03:32.146 --> 00:03:34.612
Einstein came.
There was a theory of

00:03:34.612 --> 00:03:38.653
relativity at the time of Newton
and that's where I want to

00:03:38.653 --> 00:03:41.742
begin.
Relativity is not a new idea at

00:03:41.742 --> 00:03:45.628
all, it's an old one.
And the old idea can be

00:03:45.628 --> 00:03:50.648
illustrated in this way and it
will agree with your own

00:03:50.648 --> 00:03:54.277
experience.
So, the standard technique for

00:03:54.277 --> 00:03:58.389
all of relativity is to get
these high speed trains.

00:03:58.389 --> 00:04:01.020
I'm going to have our own high
speed train;

00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:06.020
this is the top view of the
train.

00:04:06.020 --> 00:04:09.005
And like in everything I do,
we'll get away with the lowest

00:04:09.005 --> 00:04:12.004
number of dimensions,
which happens to be this one

00:04:12.004 --> 00:04:15.050
spatial dimension and of course
there is time.

00:04:15.050 --> 00:04:17.400
So, the train is moving along
the x axis.

00:04:17.400 --> 00:04:24.121
You are in this train.
You board the train and all the

00:04:24.121 --> 00:04:30.000
blinds are closed because you
don't want to look outside.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.360
That's not because you're
traveling through some parts of

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:36.617
New Jersey;
you don't want to look outside

00:04:36.617 --> 00:04:41.440
for this particular experiment.
You get into the train,

00:04:41.440 --> 00:04:46.560
you settle down and you explore
the world around you.

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:50.046
You pour yourself a drink,
you play pool,

00:04:50.046 --> 00:04:54.230
you juggle some ping pong
balls, tennis balls,

00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:58.033
and you have a certain
awareness of what's happening,

00:04:58.033 --> 00:05:01.910
namely, your understanding of
the mechanical world,

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:06.692
and then you go to sleep.
When you are sleeping,

00:05:06.692 --> 00:05:12.914
some unseen hand gives to this
train a large velocity,

00:05:12.914 --> 00:05:16.906
200 miles an hour.
The question is,

00:05:16.906 --> 00:05:21.390
"When you wake up,
can you tell if you're moving

00:05:21.390 --> 00:05:24.800
or not?"
That's the whole question.

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:27.175
Will this speed,
whatever I gave you,

00:05:27.175 --> 00:05:31.069
200 miles per hour--will it do
anything to you in this train

00:05:31.069 --> 00:05:35.867
that will betray that velocity?
So, when you wake up will you

00:05:35.867 --> 00:05:39.066
say I'm moving or not?
Now, you might say,

00:05:39.066 --> 00:05:42.939
I'm not moving because I'm on
Amtrak and I know this train is

00:05:42.939 --> 00:05:45.950
not going anywhere.
That kind of sociological

00:05:45.950 --> 00:05:48.623
reason, by the way,
there are many of them,

00:05:48.623 --> 00:05:50.823
you cannot invoke.
You can only say,

00:05:50.823 --> 00:05:53.959
"I'm on this train.
Is anything different?"

00:05:53.959 --> 00:05:57.160
And the claim is that nothing
will be different.

00:05:57.160 --> 00:05:59.139
You just will not know you are
moving.

00:05:59.139 --> 00:06:04.849
Now, if the train picks up
speed, or slows down,

00:06:04.849 --> 00:06:09.165
you will know right away.
If it picks up speed or

00:06:09.165 --> 00:06:11.868
accelerates, you find yourself
pushed against the back of the

00:06:11.868 --> 00:06:13.850
seat or if the driver slams on
the brake,

00:06:13.850 --> 00:06:17.569
you will slam into the front of
the seat in front of you.

00:06:17.569 --> 00:06:20.812
No one is saying that when the
motion is accelerated,

00:06:20.812 --> 00:06:24.021
you will not know.
Accelerated motion can be

00:06:24.021 --> 00:06:28.100
detected in a closed train
without looking outside.

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:32.184
The question is uniform
velocity, no matter how high,

00:06:32.184 --> 00:06:35.350
can that be perceived?
Can that be detected?

00:06:35.350 --> 00:06:40.057
So, at the time of Galileo and
Newton everybody agreed that you

00:06:40.057 --> 00:06:43.810
cannot detect it.
Remember that if you started

00:06:43.810 --> 00:06:49.009
out and Newton's laws worked for
you, you are called an inertial

00:06:49.009 --> 00:06:51.578
observer.
One of the laws you want is,

00:06:51.578 --> 00:06:54.509
if you leave something,
it should stay where it is.

00:06:54.509 --> 00:06:58.009
When the train is accelerating,
that won't be true.

00:06:58.009 --> 00:07:00.686
You leave things on the floor
when it's accelerating,

00:07:00.686 --> 00:07:03.483
things will slide backwards.
So, with no apparent force

00:07:03.483 --> 00:07:05.074
acting on it,
things will begin to

00:07:05.074 --> 00:07:07.810
accelerate;
that's a non-inertial frame.

00:07:07.810 --> 00:07:10.908
We are not interested in that.
You started out as an observer

00:07:10.908 --> 00:07:14.115
for whom the laws of Newton
work, the laws of inertia work,

00:07:14.115 --> 00:07:16.769
F = ma, then you go to sleep
and you wake up.

00:07:16.769 --> 00:07:19.521
So, when I said everything
looks the same,

00:07:19.521 --> 00:07:23.615
I really meant that the laws of
Newton continue to be the same

00:07:23.615 --> 00:07:26.770
because if the laws of Newton
are the same,

00:07:26.770 --> 00:07:29.691
everything will look the same.
That's what it means to say

00:07:29.691 --> 00:07:32.498
"everything looks the same."
Our expectations of what

00:07:32.498 --> 00:07:35.962
happens when I throw it up or
what happens when two billiard

00:07:35.962 --> 00:07:38.545
balls collide,
everything is connected to the

00:07:38.545 --> 00:07:40.999
laws of Newton.
So, the claim is,

00:07:40.999 --> 00:07:45.289
the laws of Newton will be
unchanged when this velocity is

00:07:45.289 --> 00:07:48.706
added on to you.
Now, we should be clear about

00:07:48.706 --> 00:07:51.467
one thing.
If there is a train next to you

00:07:51.467 --> 00:07:54.963
in the beginning -- let me just
put it on this side for

00:07:54.963 --> 00:07:58.783
convenience -- and you got in
and you boarded this train but

00:07:58.783 --> 00:08:02.149
you looked at this train and it
was not moving.

00:08:02.149 --> 00:08:04.592
If you lift the blind and look
through, you'll see the other

00:08:04.592 --> 00:08:06.952
train and there's another
passenger in the other train and

00:08:06.952 --> 00:08:10.120
you look at each other,
you're not moving.

00:08:10.120 --> 00:08:14.534
When you wake up after this
brief nap, you find when you

00:08:14.534 --> 00:08:19.509
look outside the other train is
moving at 200 miles an hour.

00:08:19.509 --> 00:08:23.603
The question is,
"Can you tell if it's you who's

00:08:23.603 --> 00:08:27.000
responsible for this relative
motion,

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:30.466
or maybe nothing happened to
you and the other train is

00:08:30.466 --> 00:08:34.854
moving the opposite way?"
And the claim of relativity is

00:08:34.854 --> 00:08:39.092
that you really cannot tell.
You can tell there is motion

00:08:39.092 --> 00:08:42.019
between the two trains that
wasn't there before.

00:08:42.019 --> 00:08:45.612
That's very clear if you look
outside but there is no way to

00:08:45.612 --> 00:08:48.840
tell what actually happened when
you were sleeping.

00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:51.533
Whether you were given the
velocity of 200 to the right or

00:08:51.533 --> 00:08:54.226
the other train was given a
velocity of 200 to the left or

00:08:54.226 --> 00:08:57.340
maybe a combination of the two,
you just cannot tell.

00:08:57.340 --> 00:09:00.865
That's the word "relative."
So far -- I didn't tell you --

00:09:00.865 --> 00:09:04.159
if you have only one train,
what I told you earlier,

00:09:04.159 --> 00:09:07.770
is that uniform velocity does
not leave its imprint on

00:09:07.770 --> 00:09:10.776
anything you can measure.
If you look outside,

00:09:10.776 --> 00:09:13.751
of course you can see the
motion of the other train,

00:09:13.751 --> 00:09:16.259
but you still cannot tell who
is moving.

00:09:16.259 --> 00:09:20.639
You cannot distinguish between
different possibilities.

00:09:20.639 --> 00:09:24.409
So, you have every right to
insist that you are not moving

00:09:24.409 --> 00:09:27.649
and the other train is moving
the opposite way.

00:09:27.649 --> 00:09:32.105
Once again, you can make this
argument only for uniform

00:09:32.105 --> 00:09:35.789
relative motion.
If your train is accelerating,

00:09:35.789 --> 00:09:39.236
now I'm saying it as if it is
an absolute thing,

00:09:39.236 --> 00:09:41.007
and it is.
You cannot say,

00:09:41.007 --> 00:09:43.897
"I'm not accelerating,
the other train is accelerating

00:09:43.897 --> 00:09:47.030
in the other direction."
You cannot say that because

00:09:47.030 --> 00:09:50.722
you're the one who is barfing up
and throwing up and slamming

00:09:50.722 --> 00:09:53.333
your head on the wall;
nothing is happening to the

00:09:53.333 --> 00:09:55.646
other person.
You cannot say "I'm still in

00:09:55.646 --> 00:09:58.218
the same frame,
you are going the opposite

00:09:58.218 --> 00:09:59.755
way."
If you are going the opposite

00:09:59.755 --> 00:10:02.851
way, why am I throwing up?
Or if you are in a rocket and

00:10:02.851 --> 00:10:07.409
the rocket's taking off and the
G forces are enormous,

00:10:07.409 --> 00:10:09.984
many times your weight,
it is the astronauts who are

00:10:09.984 --> 00:10:13.269
going through the discomfort.
At that time they cannot say we

00:10:13.269 --> 00:10:16.430
are at rest and everyone is
going the opposite way because

00:10:16.430 --> 00:10:18.759
no one else is in danger,
but they are.

00:10:18.759 --> 00:10:21.090
So, accelerated motion will
produce effects.

00:10:21.090 --> 00:10:23.259
You cannot talk your way out of
that.

00:10:23.259 --> 00:10:26.712
But uniform velocity will
produce no effects on you and no

00:10:26.712 --> 00:10:30.345
effects on the other person.
You can detect relative motion

00:10:30.345 --> 00:10:33.915
but you cannot in any sense
maintain that you are moving and

00:10:33.915 --> 00:10:36.820
he's not or that he's moving and
you are not.

00:10:36.820 --> 00:10:38.527
You can say,
"I am at rest,

00:10:38.527 --> 00:10:42.007
things are the same as before,
the train is moving the

00:10:42.007 --> 00:10:45.419
opposite way."
Now, if you go in the Amtrak

00:10:45.419 --> 00:10:49.720
and you look outside and you
don't see another train,

00:10:49.720 --> 00:10:52.101
but you see the landscape,
you see trees and cows and

00:10:52.101 --> 00:10:54.528
everything, going at 200 miles
an hour in the opposite

00:10:54.528 --> 00:10:57.329
direction,
you have some reason to believe

00:10:57.329 --> 00:11:01.440
that probably the ground is not
moving and you are moving.

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:07.015
But that's just based on what I
called earlier some sociological

00:11:07.015 --> 00:11:08.875
factors.
In other words,

00:11:08.875 --> 00:11:12.519
it's completely possible to
devise an experiment in which

00:11:12.519 --> 00:11:16.097
somebody puts the whole
landscape on wheels and when you

00:11:16.097 --> 00:11:19.945
go to sleep the landscapes,
cows and trees are made to move

00:11:19.945 --> 00:11:22.043
the opposite way.
Not very likely,

00:11:22.043 --> 00:11:25.800
but that's because we know in
practice no one is going to

00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.350
bother to do that just to fool
you.

00:11:28.350 --> 00:11:31.090
But if that did happen,
you won't know the difference.

00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:33.884
So, the reason we rule that out
is we know some extraneous

00:11:33.884 --> 00:11:36.139
things not connected to the laws
of physics.

00:11:36.139 --> 00:11:39.116
That's why we don't like to
open the window and look at the

00:11:39.116 --> 00:11:41.169
landscape because then we have a
bias.

00:11:41.169 --> 00:11:44.066
Open the window and look at
another train and you just won't

00:11:44.066 --> 00:11:46.416
know.
That is the principle of

00:11:46.416 --> 00:11:50.848
relativity, that uniform motion
between two observers,

00:11:50.848 --> 00:11:54.360
both of whom are inertial,
is relative.

00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:56.789
Each one can insist that he or
she is not moving;

00:11:56.789 --> 00:11:59.299
the other person is the one who
is moving.

00:11:59.299 --> 00:12:02.233
Of course, now,
if the two, in reality,

00:12:02.233 --> 00:12:06.634
if the two trains were at
rest--Let's imagine my train got

00:12:06.634 --> 00:12:09.536
accelerated.
So, during the time it was

00:12:09.536 --> 00:12:12.997
accelerated, I would know,
but if I was sleeping at the

00:12:12.997 --> 00:12:15.132
time,
I don't know and when I wake up

00:12:15.132 --> 00:12:18.220
and the acceleration is gone and
the velocity is constant,

00:12:18.220 --> 00:12:20.490
that's when I say,
"I just cannot tell."

00:12:20.490 --> 00:12:25.687
All right.
Now, let's show once and for

00:12:25.687 --> 00:12:31.129
all that the laws of Newton are
not going to be modified.

00:12:31.129 --> 00:12:34.229
So, you find the laws of Newton
before you go to sleep,

00:12:34.229 --> 00:12:36.065
you wake up,
you find them again,

00:12:36.065 --> 00:12:38.830
you'll get the same laws;
that's the claim.

00:12:38.830 --> 00:12:41.886
I hope you understand that all
the mechanical things you see in

00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:44.450
the world around you come just
from F = ma.

00:12:44.450 --> 00:12:47.998
We have seen projectiles and
collision of billiard balls and

00:12:47.998 --> 00:12:50.360
rockets;
they're all Newtonian mechanics.

00:12:50.360 --> 00:12:53.856
So, to say that things will
look the same is to say the laws

00:12:53.856 --> 00:12:57.471
of Newton that you will deduce
before and after waking up will

00:12:57.471 --> 00:13:00.340
be the same.
So, let's show that.

00:13:00.340 --> 00:13:02.504
When you show that,
you're really done with it once

00:13:02.504 --> 00:13:04.960
and for all.
So, let's do the following.

00:13:04.960 --> 00:13:11.930
Here is the x axis and
here is my frame of reference.

00:13:11.930 --> 00:13:14.710
This is my x axis.
Let's call this the origin.

00:13:14.710 --> 00:13:18.149
The frame goes to negative and
positive x values.

00:13:18.149 --> 00:13:22.790
Pick some object sitting at the
point x.

00:13:27.470 --> 00:13:31.149
Now, we are going to first
define the notion of an event.

00:13:31.149 --> 00:13:35.749
An event is something that
happens at a certain place at a

00:13:35.749 --> 00:13:40.879
certain time;
that's called an event.

00:13:40.879 --> 00:13:43.242
For example,
if there's a little firecracker

00:13:43.242 --> 00:13:46.373
going off somewhere at some
time, the x is where it

00:13:46.373 --> 00:13:49.120
happened and the t is
when it happened.

00:13:49.120 --> 00:13:54.445
So, this is space-time.
Once again, space-time does not

00:13:54.445 --> 00:13:56.360
require Einstein coming in at
all.

00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:58.980
We have known for thousands of
years that if you want to set up

00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:01.436
a meeting with somebody,
you've got to say where and

00:14:01.436 --> 00:14:04.399
you've got to say when and
things do happen in space-time.

00:14:04.399 --> 00:14:06.484
The fact that you need x
and t,

00:14:06.484 --> 00:14:08.899
or, if you're living in three
spatial dimensions,

00:14:08.899 --> 00:14:11.122
the fact that you need
x, y,

00:14:11.122 --> 00:14:13.019
z and t is not
new.

00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:17.279
That is not the revolution
Einstein created.

00:14:17.279 --> 00:14:19.995
The fact that you need four
coordinates to label an event is

00:14:19.995 --> 00:14:22.957
nothing new.
What he did that is new will be

00:14:22.957 --> 00:14:26.181
clear later.
So, does everyone understand

00:14:26.181 --> 00:14:28.620
what an event means?
Okay?

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:32.049
An event is something that
happens and to say exactly where

00:14:32.049 --> 00:14:34.977
and when it happened,
in our world of one dimension,

00:14:34.977 --> 00:14:37.590
we give it an x and we
give it a t.

00:14:37.590 --> 00:14:41.553
Now, that's me,
and I'm going to give my frame

00:14:41.553 --> 00:14:46.370
of reference the name S.
It turns out S is not

00:14:46.370 --> 00:14:49.947
just based on just my name.
This is the canonical name for

00:14:49.947 --> 00:14:52.393
two observers,
one is called S and one

00:14:52.393 --> 00:14:55.054
is called S prime.
So, S prime,

00:14:55.054 --> 00:14:58.811
let's say, is you.
So, your frame of reference is

00:14:58.811 --> 00:15:03.230
going to be taken to be sliding
relative to mine.

00:15:03.230 --> 00:15:08.889
So, let's draw a y axis
here.

00:15:08.889 --> 00:15:11.805
We don't really deal with the
y coordinate but just to

00:15:11.805 --> 00:15:14.090
give you a feeling,
this is my y axis;

00:15:14.090 --> 00:15:16.299
that's my x axis;
this is my origin.

00:15:16.299 --> 00:15:18.679
y is not going to play a
big role.

00:15:18.679 --> 00:15:23.211
Now, you are sliding this way,
to the right,

00:15:23.211 --> 00:15:29.430
and your speed or velocity is
always denoted by u.

00:15:33.330 --> 00:15:36.131
Some number of meters per
second, you are zooming to the

00:15:36.131 --> 00:15:42.250
right at some speed u.
So, imagine now you are going

00:15:42.250 --> 00:15:45.669
past me.
At some instant--I'm sitting

00:15:45.669 --> 00:15:49.257
here at the origin of
coordinates, you cross me and

00:15:49.257 --> 00:15:52.629
then a little later you are
somewhere there.

00:15:52.629 --> 00:15:54.450
So, that's your y frame
axis;

00:15:54.450 --> 00:15:58.316
that's your origin.
And the same event you say has

00:15:58.316 --> 00:16:00.420
a coordinate x prime.

00:16:04.049 --> 00:16:07.594
We arrange it so that when you
zoom past me,

00:16:07.594 --> 00:16:12.210
you set your clock to zero and
