00:19:22.556 --> 00:19:24.570
u times t.

00:19:29.190 --> 00:19:32.484
So, the distance from your
origin for this event,

00:19:32.484 --> 00:19:35.780
I maintain is x prime is
x - ut.

00:19:43.049 --> 00:19:45.110
Again, I want all of you to
follow everything.

00:19:45.110 --> 00:19:49.473
These are all simple notions.
Our origins coincided at zero

00:19:49.473 --> 00:19:53.619
time for the event that occurs
at time t.

00:19:53.619 --> 00:19:56.200
Therefore, in a sense,
you are rushing toward the

00:19:56.200 --> 00:19:57.736
event.
You've gone a distance

00:19:57.736 --> 00:20:00.044
ut.
Therefore, the distance from

00:20:00.044 --> 00:20:03.865
your origin to the event will be
less than mine by this amount

00:20:03.865 --> 00:20:07.250
ut.
This is the law of

00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:14.960
transformation of coordinates in
Newtonian mechanics.

00:20:14.960 --> 00:20:19.108
If you have an event--if you
want, formally,

00:20:19.108 --> 00:20:24.125
you can define it time,
t prime for the primed

00:20:24.125 --> 00:20:26.565
observer.
It goes without saying that

00:20:26.565 --> 00:20:28.410
t prime and t are
the same.

00:20:28.410 --> 00:20:31.450
There's no notion of time for
