00:20:47.004 --> 00:20:50.131
after our meeting for me and
it's going to be 5 seconds after

00:20:50.131 --> 00:20:53.467
the meeting for you.
The time difference between two

00:20:53.467 --> 00:20:55.880
events is the same for all
people.

00:20:55.880 --> 00:20:58.560
This is called the Galilean
transformation.

00:21:06.420 --> 00:21:09.750
What are the consequences of
Galilean transformation?

00:21:09.750 --> 00:21:12.133
Well, let's look at the fact
that x prime is x -

00:21:12.133 --> 00:21:12.510
ut.

00:21:19.759 --> 00:21:21.789
Remember, everything is varying
with time.

00:21:21.789 --> 00:21:24.879
So x prime is a function
of time and x is a

00:21:24.879 --> 00:21:27.362
function of time,
if you are watching a moving

00:21:27.362 --> 00:21:31.451
particle.
Suppose this firecracker is not

00:21:31.451 --> 00:21:36.019
just one event,
but it's a moving object.

00:21:36.019 --> 00:21:37.960
Let's give the object some
speed;

00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:41.062
