Then the velocity,

00:21:41.062 --> 00:21:48.222
according to me--I'm going to
call v as dx/dt is

00:21:48.222 --> 00:21:53.882
the velocity.
Let's just call it a bullet,

00:21:53.882 --> 00:21:59.502
according to S.
Then w -- it's the

00:21:59.502 --> 00:22:05.331
standard name -- is the velocity
of the bullet according to

00:22:05.331 --> 00:22:08.568
S prime.
So, what I've done is,

00:22:08.568 --> 00:22:12.335
I first took one event and I
gave it some coordinates and I

00:22:12.335 --> 00:22:16.101
told you how to transform the
coordinate from one person to

00:22:16.101 --> 00:22:19.431
the other person.
But now, take that point

00:22:19.431 --> 00:22:23.790
x not to be a fixed
location but a moving object,

00:22:23.790 --> 00:22:27.990
so that as a function of time
that body is moving.

00:22:27.990 --> 00:22:32.962
Then its velocity at any time
is dx prime dt

00:22:32.962 --> 00:22:36.708
according to you;
that is the dx/dt

00:22:36.708 --> 00:22:40.623
according to me,
minus the derivative of this,

00:22:40.623 --> 00:22:46.230
