you wake up in the train,
you will look at the world

00:30:47.345 --> 00:30:49.956
around you, it will look
different because F ≠

00:30:49.956 --> 00:30:51.625
ma.
You will conclude,

00:30:51.625 --> 00:30:53.619
when I went to sleep it was
F = ma;

00:30:53.619 --> 00:30:55.396
when I got up,
F ≠ ma,

00:30:55.396 --> 00:30:59.016
the train is moving.
So, you will have to conclude

00:30:59.016 --> 00:31:02.849
that uniform velocity makes
detectable changes.

00:31:02.849 --> 00:31:06.625
And if you look outside the
train, to the other train,

00:31:06.625 --> 00:31:09.190
the other train's going
backwards.

00:31:09.190 --> 00:31:12.000
You can now no longer say,
"You're going the other way,

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:14.342
I'm not moving",
because the other person will

00:31:14.342 --> 00:31:16.580
say, "Hey, F = ma works
for me."

00:31:16.580 --> 00:31:19.077
It doesn't work for you.
So, you're the guy who's

00:31:19.077 --> 00:31:21.253
moving."
So, you've lost the equal

00:31:21.253 --> 00:31:25.321
status with other inertial
observers because those for whom

00:31:25.321 --> 00:31:29.809
F = ma worked will say
they're not moving and for you,

00:31:29.809 --> 00:31:32.120
it doesn't work,
so you will have to concede you

00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:34.039
are moving.
So, uniform velocity,

00:31:34.039 --> 00:31:36.965
if it makes perceptible
changes, can no longer be

00:31:36.965 --> 00:31:40.318
considered as relative.
It's absolute and if you and I

00:31:40.318 --> 00:31:43.323
find each other moving,
there may be a real sense in

00:31:43.323 --> 00:31:45.740
which I am at rest and you are
moving,

00:31:45.740 --> 00:31:48.600
because for me F = ma
works and for you it doesn't.

00:31:48.600 --> 00:31:51.476
Well, that's not what happens.
In real life,

00:31:51.476 --> 00:31:54.338
you find it works for both of
these and either of us can

00:31:54.338 --> 00:31:58.764
maintain we are not moving.
So now, you've got to fast

00:31:58.764 --> 00:32:02.957
forward to about 300 years.
This goes on,

00:32:02.957 --> 00:32:07.813
no problem with this principle
of relativity and 300 years

00:32:07.813 --> 00:32:10.202
later,
people have discovered

00:32:10.202 --> 00:32:13.816
electricity and magnetism and
electromagnetism and

00:32:13.816 --> 00:32:17.609
electromagnetic waves,
which they identify as light.

00:32:17.609 --> 00:32:22.487
And then, it was discovered
that what you and I call light

00:32:22.487 --> 00:32:27.450
is just electric and magnetic
fields traveling in space.

00:32:27.450 --> 00:32:29.683
You don't have to know what
electro-magnetic fields are

00:32:29.683 --> 00:32:31.473
right now.
They are some measurable

00:32:31.473 --> 00:32:33.680
phenomenon.
They are like waves.

00:32:33.680 --> 00:32:37.696
And the waves have a certain
velocity that Maxwell calculated

00:32:37.696 --> 00:32:41.847
and that velocity is this famous
number 3 times 10 to the eight

00:32:41.847 --> 00:32:45.128
meters per second.
And the question was,

00:32:45.128 --> 00:32:47.970
"For whom is this the
velocity?"

00:32:47.970 --> 00:32:50.838
For example,
you can do a calculation of

00:32:50.838 --> 00:32:54.295
waves on a string,
something we'll be able to do

00:32:54.295 --> 00:32:57.333
in our course.
Waves on a string will be some

00:32:57.333 --> 00:33:00.473
answer that depends on the
tension on the string and the

00:33:00.473 --> 00:33:04.014
mass density of the string and
that's the velocity as seen by a

00:33:04.014 --> 00:33:06.470
person for whom the string is at
rest.

00:33:06.470 --> 00:33:10.276
But if you calculate the waves
of sound in this room -- I talk

00:33:10.276 --> 00:33:13.832
to you, you hear me slightly
later -- the time it takes to

00:33:13.832 --> 00:33:16.890
travel is the velocity of sound
in this room.

00:33:16.890 --> 00:33:21.438
That is calculated with respect
to the air in this room because

00:33:21.438 --> 00:33:25.398
the waves travel in the air.
In fact, the fact that all of

00:33:25.398 --> 00:33:28.672
us are sitting on the planet,
which itself is moving at

00:33:28.672 --> 00:33:30.732
whatever,
1,100 miles per second,

00:33:30.732 --> 00:33:32.992
doesn't matter,
because the air is being

00:33:32.992 --> 00:33:36.470
carried along so even if the
Earth came to a sudden halt,

00:33:36.470 --> 00:33:38.826
as far as the velocity of sound
in this room is concerned,

00:33:38.826 --> 00:33:40.819
it won't matter,
because we are carrying the

00:33:40.819 --> 00:33:44.179
medium with us.
So, people wanted to know what

00:33:44.179 --> 00:33:48.196
is the medium which carries the
waves of light,

00:33:48.196 --> 00:33:51.520
electromagnetic waves?
First of all,

00:33:51.520 --> 00:33:56.081
the medium is everywhere
because--How do we know it's

00:33:56.081 --> 00:33:58.920
everywhere?
Can anybody tell me?

00:34:03.590 --> 00:34:05.244
Yes?
Student: It travels

00:34:05.244 --> 00:34:06.487
through the vacuum of space.
Professor Ramamurti

00:34:06.487 --> 00:34:07.690
Shankar: Right.
It travels in the vacuum of

00:34:07.690 --> 00:34:08.969
space.
We can see the Sun;

00:34:08.969 --> 00:34:10.816
we can see the stars,
so we know the medium is

00:34:10.816 --> 00:34:13.032
everywhere.
Then, you can sort of ask,

00:34:13.032 --> 00:34:16.439
"How dense is the medium?"
It turns out that the denser

00:34:16.439 --> 00:34:18.987
the medium, the more rapidly
signals travel,

00:34:18.987 --> 00:34:21.239
in most of the things that we
know.

00:34:21.239 --> 00:34:24.329
For example,
when we look at waves in sound

00:34:24.329 --> 00:34:27.639
and when we look at sound waves
in a solid,

00:34:27.639 --> 00:34:29.832
or in iron, you find in a very
dense material,

00:34:29.832 --> 00:34:32.583
that the velocity is very high.
S,o this medium,

00:34:32.583 --> 00:34:35.872
which is called "ether," would
have to be very,

00:34:35.872 --> 00:34:40.090
very dense to support waves of
this incredible velocity.

00:34:40.090 --> 00:34:43.979
But then, planets have been
moving through this medium for

00:34:43.979 --> 00:34:46.640
years and years and not slowing
down.

00:34:46.640 --> 00:34:50.480
It's a very peculiar medium.
But it has to be everywhere so

00:34:50.480 --> 00:34:54.028
we are all immersed in this
medium because we are able to

00:34:54.028 --> 00:34:57.639
send light signals to different
parts of the universe.

00:34:57.639 --> 00:35:02.017
And the question is,
"How fast is the Earth moving

00:35:02.017 --> 00:35:06.330
relative to this medium?"
You understand?

00:35:06.330 --> 00:35:10.651
This medium is all pervasive.
We know that we can see the

00:35:10.651 --> 00:35:13.699
stars so it's going all the way
up to the stars and beyond.

00:35:13.699 --> 00:35:17.239
And we are immersed in this and
we are drifting around in space.

00:35:17.239 --> 00:35:19.969
What is our speed relative to
the medium?

00:35:19.969 --> 00:35:21.639
That's the question that was
asked.

00:35:21.639 --> 00:35:25.201
Well, to find the speed
relative to the medium,

00:35:25.201 --> 00:35:30.079
you calculate the velocity in
the medium by Maxwell's theory.

00:35:30.079 --> 00:35:33.940
So, here's the medium in which
waves travel at a certain speed.

00:35:33.940 --> 00:35:37.409
This is planet Earth going
around the Sun.

00:35:37.409 --> 00:35:40.172
At some instant,
you will have a certain

00:35:40.172 --> 00:35:43.608
velocity with respect to ether.
And therefore,

00:35:43.608 --> 00:35:48.082
the velocity of light as seen
by you will be modified from

00:35:48.082 --> 00:35:51.592
c to c - V.
In particular,

00:35:51.592 --> 00:35:56.750
suppose the waves are traveling
to the right in ether.

00:35:56.750 --> 00:35:59.104
Let me draw it this way.
The Earth is going at this

00:35:59.104 --> 00:36:02.560
instant at the speed V.
We expect the speed to be c

00:36:02.560 --> 00:36:06.671
- V because part of the
speed is neutralized because you

00:36:06.671 --> 00:36:10.580
are going along with the waves.
You'll see a slower velocity.

00:36:13.909 --> 00:36:16.980
So, Mr.
Michelson and his assistant

00:36:16.980 --> 00:36:23.965
Morley--they did the experiment.
And they got the answer equal

00:36:23.965 --> 00:36:27.610
to c.
What does that mean?

00:36:27.610 --> 00:36:31.782
Student: The speed of
light [inaudible]

00:36:31.782 --> 00:36:35.305
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No,

00:36:35.305 --> 00:36:39.570
no, but you cannot jump to that
right now.

00:36:39.570 --> 00:36:44.439
If you are following Newtonian
physics, your expectation is,

00:36:44.439 --> 00:36:47.429
it should be c - V.
Yes?

00:36:47.429 --> 00:36:52.619
Student: It means that
there is no ether.

00:36:52.619 --> 00:36:53.804
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Well,

00:36:53.804 --> 00:36:55.165
that's--not so fast,
but it certainly means the

00:36:55.165 --> 00:36:56.853
following.
Well, there's a simpler answer

00:36:56.853 --> 00:36:58.329
than that.
Yes?

00:36:58.329 --> 00:37:00.818
Student: It means that
the Earth is moving with respect

00:37:00.818 --> 00:37:01.962
to the ether.
Professor Ramamurti

00:37:01.962 --> 00:37:03.860
Shankar: At what speed?
Student: Zero.

00:37:03.860 --> 00:37:04.789
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Zero.

00:37:04.789 --> 00:37:07.139
Because you don't have
to--Look, you guys are ready to

00:37:07.139 --> 00:37:09.400
overthrow everything because you
know the answer.

00:37:09.400 --> 00:37:14.418
But you've got to put yourself
in the place of somebody in the

00:37:14.418 --> 00:37:16.920
early 1900s.
There's no reason to overthrow

00:37:16.920 --> 00:37:18.395
anything.
The answer is,

00:37:18.395 --> 00:37:22.435
you're going at the speed zero.
Of course, you realize,

00:37:22.435 --> 00:37:26.858
that it is incredibly fortunate
that on the one day Michelson

00:37:26.858 --> 00:37:31.102
wants to do the experiment,
we happen to be at rest with

00:37:31.102 --> 00:37:34.059
respect to the ether.
Fine.

00:37:34.059 --> 00:37:37.726
But we know that luck is not
going to last forever because

00:37:37.726 --> 00:37:42.860
you are going around the Sun.
On a particular day may be.

00:37:42.860 --> 00:37:46.156
But that velocity was such that
on that day the Earth was at

00:37:46.156 --> 00:37:49.184
rest with respect to the ether.
It's clear that six months

00:37:49.184 --> 00:37:51.188
later, when we are going the
other direction,

00:37:51.188 --> 00:37:53.739
you cannot also be at rest with
respect to the ether.

00:37:53.739 --> 00:37:57.730
But that's what you find when
you do the experiment.

00:37:57.730 --> 00:38:01.357
You find every day you get the
same answer and you jolly well

00:38:01.357 --> 00:38:04.194
know you are not at rest.
You are moving around the Sun

00:38:04.194 --> 00:38:05.210
for sure.
Yes?

00:38:05.210 --> 00:38:07.281
Student: Did they
postulate a drag for the Earth

00:38:07.281 --> 00:38:08.854
turning [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:38:08.854 --> 00:38:10.966
Shankar: Yes.
So, people tried other

00:38:10.966 --> 00:38:13.284
solutions.
But it is simply a fact that

00:38:13.284 --> 00:38:16.612
when you move one way or six
months later in the opposite

00:38:16.612 --> 00:38:19.050
way, you get the same answer
c.

00:38:19.050 --> 00:38:23.358
So, one possibility is,
you don't want--Look,

00:38:23.358 --> 00:38:28.449
don't be ready to do
revolutions, try to avoid it.

00:38:28.449 --> 00:38:31.500
So, one answer is,
look at the speed of sound.

00:38:31.500 --> 00:38:35.375
You and I talked to each other
then and we talked to each other

00:38:35.375 --> 00:38:38.239
six months from now;
we get the same speed of sound.

00:38:38.239 --> 00:38:40.262
The speed of sound is published
in textbooks,

00:38:40.262 --> 00:38:41.703
right?
Seven hundred and something

00:38:41.703 --> 00:38:44.262
miles per hour.
How come that doesn't change

00:38:44.262 --> 00:38:47.624
from day to day?
Anybody here on this side can

00:38:47.624 --> 00:38:52.165
tell me why the speed of sound
doesn't change from day to day

00:38:52.165 --> 00:38:57.210
even though we are moving?
No one here can guess?

00:38:57.210 --> 00:39:00.167
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:39:00.167 --> 00:39:02.159
Shankar: No,
we are moving.

00:39:02.159 --> 00:39:04.737
Even six months from now,
we get the same speed of sound

00:39:04.737 --> 00:39:06.631
in this room.
When I talk to you,

00:39:06.631 --> 00:39:09.139
does it matter what time of
year it is?

00:39:09.139 --> 00:39:12.750
Student: The medium is
moving along with us?

00:39:12.750 --> 00:39:13.613
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Yes,

00:39:13.613 --> 00:39:15.309
we are carrying air.
As the Earth moves through

00:39:15.309 --> 00:39:18.194
space, it carries the air with
you and the speed of the wave is

00:39:18.194 --> 00:39:20.750
with respect to the medium.
If you can carry the medium

00:39:20.750 --> 00:39:23.200
with you, then it doesn't matter
how fast you're moving.

00:39:23.200 --> 00:39:26.847
So, they tried that.
They tried to argue that the

00:39:26.847 --> 00:39:31.000
Earth carries ether with it the
way it carries air with it.

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:34.819
Then, it's not an accident you
are at rest with respect to the

00:39:34.819 --> 00:39:37.449
ether because you're taking it
with you.

00:39:37.449 --> 00:39:40.390
But it's very easy to show by
looking at distant stars that

00:39:40.390 --> 00:39:43.259
you cannot be doing that.
I don't have time to tell you

00:39:43.259 --> 00:39:47.470
why that is true.
So, you cannot take the ether

00:39:47.470 --> 00:39:54.483
with you and you cannot leave it
behind, and that's the impasse

00:39:54.483 --> 00:39:58.679
people were in.
So, it's as if there's a car

00:39:58.679 --> 00:40:02.920
that's going to the right at a
certain speed c.

00:40:02.920 --> 00:40:06.530
You move to the right at some
speed, maybe c/2.

00:40:06.530 --> 00:40:09.180
I expect you to get a speed
c/2.

00:40:09.180 --> 00:40:13.181
But you keep getting c.
You go three fourths of the

00:40:13.181 --> 00:40:15.638
velocity of light;
you still get the velocity of

00:40:15.638 --> 00:40:18.899
light.
That is very contrary to what

00:40:18.899 --> 00:40:21.722
we believe.
In fact, that's in violent

00:40:21.722 --> 00:40:25.257
opposition to this law here.
If this V were not a

00:40:25.257 --> 00:40:28.688
bullet but a light beam,
suppose for me traveling at a

00:40:28.688 --> 00:40:32.313
speed c and you're
traveling to the right at speed

00:40:32.313 --> 00:40:35.190
u,
you should get c - u.

00:40:35.190 --> 00:40:37.971
That's the inevitable
consequence of Newtonian

00:40:37.971 --> 00:40:40.380
physics.
And you don't get that.

00:40:40.380 --> 00:40:45.460
And that was a big problem.
So, people tried to fix it up

00:40:45.460 --> 00:40:49.940
by doing different models of
ether, none of which worked.

00:40:49.940 --> 00:40:54.119
And nobody knew why light is
behaving in this peculiar

00:40:54.119 --> 00:40:58.219
fashion, so that's when Einstein
came in and said,

00:40:58.219 --> 00:41:00.940
"I know why light is behaving
in this peculiar fashion.

00:41:00.940 --> 00:41:04.736
It is behaving in this way
because if it didn't behave in

00:41:04.736 --> 00:41:09.210
this way, if the speed of light
depended on how fast I'm moving,

00:41:09.210 --> 00:41:13.133
then when I wake up in this
train, all I have to do is

00:41:13.133 --> 00:41:18.230
measure the speed of light.
Originally, I got some number;

00:41:18.230 --> 00:41:21.206
now I get to get a different
number and the difference will

00:41:21.206 --> 00:41:24.609
give me the speed of the train.
So, it would have been possible

00:41:24.609 --> 00:41:27.863
to detect the velocity of the
train without looking outside,

00:41:27.863 --> 00:41:30.179
just by doing an experiment
with light.

00:41:30.179 --> 00:41:34.873
So, even though mechanical laws
involving F = ma are the

00:41:34.873 --> 00:41:39.188
same, laws of electricity and
magnetism would be such that

00:41:39.188 --> 00:41:42.519
somehow they would betray your
velocity.

00:41:42.519 --> 00:41:46.475
And that would mean uniform
velocity does make an observable

00:41:46.475 --> 00:41:50.565
change because it changes the
velocity of light that you would

00:41:50.565 --> 00:41:52.504
measure.
" But conversely,

00:41:52.504 --> 00:41:56.242
the fact that you keep getting
the same answer means that

00:41:56.242 --> 00:42:00.247
electric and magnetic phenomena
are part of the conspiracy to

00:42:00.247 --> 00:42:03.550
hide your velocity.
Just like mechanical phenomena

00:42:03.550 --> 00:42:06.385
won't tell you how fast you're
moving, neither will

00:42:06.385 --> 00:42:09.233
electromagnetic phenomena.
Because to Einstein,

00:42:09.233 --> 00:42:12.785
it was very obvious that nature
would not design a system in

00:42:12.785 --> 00:42:16.457
which mechanical laws are the
same but laws of electricity are

00:42:16.457 --> 00:42:19.469
different.
So, he postulated that all

00:42:19.469 --> 00:42:24.092
phenomena, whatever be their
nature, will be unaffected by

00:42:24.092 --> 00:42:28.959
going to a frame at constant
velocity relative to the initial

00:42:28.959 --> 00:42:31.539
one.
That's a very brave postulate

00:42:31.539 --> 00:42:35.237
because it even applies to
biological phenomena about which

00:42:35.237 --> 00:42:37.659
I'm sure Einstein knew very
little.

00:42:37.659 --> 00:42:41.265
But he believed that natural
phenomena will just follow

00:42:41.265 --> 00:42:44.670
either the principle of
relativity or they won't.

00:42:44.670 --> 00:42:50.639
And that is something you
should think about.

00:42:50.639 --> 00:42:52.489
Because that was the only
reason he had.

00:42:52.489 --> 00:42:54.939
He just said,
"I don't believe chapters 1

00:42:54.939 --> 00:42:58.185
through 10 in our book obey
relativity and chapters 20

00:42:58.185 --> 00:43:00.880
through 30 where we do E&amp;M
doesn't."

00:43:00.880 --> 00:43:04.044
These are all natural phenomena
that will obey the same

00:43:04.044 --> 00:43:07.033
principle, which says all
observers that are uniform

00:43:07.033 --> 00:43:09.260
relative to motion are
equivalent.

00:43:09.260 --> 00:43:12.355
Now, that's really based on a
lot of faith and even though

00:43:12.355 --> 00:43:15.449
scientists generally are opposed
to intelligent design,

00:43:15.449 --> 00:43:20.290
we all have some bias about the
way natural laws were designed;

00:43:20.290 --> 00:43:22.869
there's no question about it.
You can talk to any practicing

00:43:22.869 --> 00:43:25.131
physicist.
We have a faith that underlying

00:43:25.131 --> 00:43:28.349
laws of nature will have a
certain elegance and a certain

00:43:28.349 --> 00:43:32.200
beauty and a certain uniformity
across all of natural phenomena.

00:43:32.200 --> 00:43:36.289
That is a faith that we have.
It's not a religious issue;

00:43:36.289 --> 00:43:38.789
otherwise, I wouldn't bring it
up in the classroom,

00:43:38.789 --> 00:43:41.289
but it is certainly the credo
of all scientists,

00:43:41.289 --> 00:43:45.384
at least all physicists,
that there is some elegance in

00:43:45.384 --> 00:43:50.010
the laws of nature and we put a
lot of money on that faith,

00:43:50.010 --> 00:43:52.490
that the laws of nature will do
this and will not do this.

00:43:52.490 --> 00:43:55.346
Who are we to say that?
Who are we to say nature

00:43:55.346 --> 00:43:58.556
wouldn't have a system in which
mechanics obeys the laws but

00:43:58.556 --> 00:44:00.570
electricity and magnetism
doesn't?

00:44:00.570 --> 00:44:03.250
We haven't run into somebody
called nature.

00:44:03.250 --> 00:44:06.158
We don't worship a certain
deity called nature but we

00:44:06.158 --> 00:44:08.340
believe the laws of nature obey
that.

00:44:08.340 --> 00:44:12.821
So, even though scientists or
physicists in particular may not

00:44:12.821 --> 00:44:15.760
believe in design by any
personal God,

00:44:15.760 --> 00:44:19.281
they do believe in this
underlying, rational system that

00:44:19.281 --> 00:44:22.357
we are trying to uncover.
You could be disproven,

00:44:22.357 --> 00:44:24.875
you could be wrong in making
the assumption,

00:44:24.875 --> 00:44:28.244
but here it was right.
It was really driven by this

00:44:28.244 --> 00:44:32.393
notion that all laws of physics
should obey the same principle

00:44:32.393 --> 00:44:35.634
of relativity.
So, Einstein's postulates are

00:44:35.634 --> 00:44:39.947
that light behaves in this way
because if it didn't behave in

00:44:39.947 --> 00:44:43.081
this way,
it would violate the principle

00:44:43.081 --> 00:44:46.109
of relativity,
whereas we know mechanical

00:44:46.109 --> 00:44:50.273
phenomena do and electrical
phenomena would not and that

00:44:50.273 --> 00:44:53.139
cannot be the case.
You have a question?

00:44:53.139 --> 00:44:59.000
Student: Why would that
not apply to the speed of sound?

00:44:59.000 --> 00:44:59.840
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Yes.

00:44:59.840 --> 00:45:02.585
Because in the case of the
speed of sound,

00:45:02.585 --> 00:45:04.929
you can take the medium with
you;

00:45:04.929 --> 00:45:07.239
there is no such experiment you
could perform.

00:45:07.239 --> 00:45:09.642
See, in the train,
if you could carry the ether

00:45:09.642 --> 00:45:12.880
with you, there's no surprise
you would get the same answer.

00:45:12.880 --> 00:45:15.116
But we know we cannot carry the
medium with us,

00:45:15.116 --> 00:45:17.449
that comes from
extra-terrestrial experiments.

00:45:17.449 --> 00:45:20.698
That's why the velocity of
sound is not elevated to a

00:45:20.698 --> 00:45:24.010
fundamental velocity on which
everybody will agree.

00:45:24.010 --> 00:45:26.547
So, the two great
postulates--You've got to know

00:45:26.547 --> 00:45:31.190
where the postulates come from.
Postulate Number 1 is simply a

00:45:31.190 --> 00:45:35.099
restatement of the relativity
principle.

00:45:35.099 --> 00:45:36.980
I'll just say it in one
sentence.

00:45:36.980 --> 00:45:42.601
Exact wording is not important.
All inertial observers are

00:45:42.601 --> 00:45:44.070
equivalent.

00:45:49.010 --> 00:45:53.380
"Equivalent" means each one of
them is as privileged as any

00:45:53.380 --> 00:45:56.619
other one to discover the laws
of nature.

00:45:56.619 --> 00:46:00.969
The laws of nature,
we found, are not an accident

00:46:00.969 --> 00:46:05.029
related to our state of motion.
If I find some laws,

00:46:05.029 --> 00:46:08.289
and you're moving relative to
me, you'll find the same laws.

00:46:08.289 --> 00:46:10.704
And if you and I find each
other in relative motion,

00:46:10.704 --> 00:46:13.639
you have as much right to claim
you are at rest and I am moving

00:46:13.639 --> 00:46:16.385
and I have as much right to
claim that I am at rest and you

00:46:16.385 --> 00:46:18.941
are moving.
There is complete symmetry

00:46:18.941 --> 00:46:22.039
between observers in uniform
relative motion.

00:46:22.039 --> 00:46:25.196
There is no symmetry between
people in non-uniform [relative]

00:46:25.196 --> 00:46:27.150
motion.
As I said, non-uniform motion

00:46:27.150 --> 00:46:30.110
creates effects which can
destroy me and not destroy you.

00:46:30.110 --> 00:46:32.879
So, no one's trying to talk
their way out of acceleration,

00:46:32.879 --> 00:46:35.600
whereas you can talk your way
out of uniform velocity.

00:46:35.600 --> 00:46:38.825
That's the first principle.
So this was there even from the

00:46:38.825 --> 00:46:41.997
time of Newton.
What is true here is that all

00:46:41.997 --> 00:46:46.153
inertial observers are
equivalent with respect to all

00:46:46.153 --> 00:46:49.910
natural phenomena,
meaning all natural laws.

00:46:53.130 --> 00:46:55.478
And that is a generalization,
when we say "all" instead of

00:46:55.478 --> 00:46:56.220
just mechanical.

00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:04.291
And the Second Postulate,
you call it a postulate because

00:47:04.291 --> 00:47:06.960
there is just no way to deduce
this,

00:47:06.960 --> 00:47:18.824
is that the velocity of light
is independent of the state of

00:47:18.824 --> 00:47:24.600
motion of the source,
of the observer, of everything.

00:47:30.110 --> 00:47:32.699
If a light beam is emitted by a
moving rocket,

00:47:32.699 --> 00:47:35.313
it doesn't matter.
If a light beam is seen in a

00:47:35.313 --> 00:47:37.090
moving rocket,
it doesn't matter.

00:47:37.090 --> 00:47:40.599
All people will get the same
answer for the velocity of

00:47:40.599 --> 00:47:42.540
light.
Student: Is there a

00:47:42.540 --> 00:47:44.889
reason why the speed of light is
constant?

00:47:44.889 --> 00:47:45.440
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No.

00:47:45.440 --> 00:47:48.937
That's why it is a postulate.
You can show a few things later

00:47:48.937 --> 00:47:50.651
on.
You can show that if there is

00:47:50.651 --> 00:47:52.529
any other speed,
which is the same for

00:47:52.529 --> 00:47:55.320
everybody, that would have to be
the speed of light.

00:47:55.320 --> 00:47:58.834
In the final theory of
relativity, there are not two or

00:47:58.834 --> 00:48:02.480
three velocities that come out
the same for everybody.

00:48:02.480 --> 00:48:05.840
There is only one velocity that
can have the same answer for all

00:48:05.840 --> 00:48:08.201
people.
That velocity is the velocity

00:48:08.201 --> 00:48:10.598
of light.
By that I don't mean it has to

00:48:10.598 --> 00:48:12.155
be light itself.
For example,

00:48:12.155 --> 00:48:14.510
gravitational waves travel at
the speed of light.

00:48:14.510 --> 00:48:18.232
It's not just the light.
It has to do with the velocity

00:48:18.232 --> 00:48:21.730
of light being a single number
which has to have the same value

00:48:21.730 --> 00:48:25.004
for everybody.
Okay, so it looks like he has

00:48:25.004 --> 00:48:29.951
solved a big problem because he
has said why light behaves this

00:48:29.951 --> 00:48:32.130
way;
light behaves this way because

00:48:32.130 --> 00:48:35.210
it is part of the big conspiracy
to hide uniform motion.

00:48:35.210 --> 00:48:41.384
But you will see that you have
made a terrible bargain because

00:48:41.384 --> 00:48:45.130
once you take these two
postulates,

00:48:45.130 --> 00:48:48.210
you have restored the
relativity principle to all

00:48:48.210 --> 00:48:50.050
phenomena.
Okay.

00:48:50.050 --> 00:48:52.949
You've gone beyond mechanical
phenomena to electro-magnetic

00:48:52.949 --> 00:48:55.648
phenomena.
But you will find that you have

00:48:55.648 --> 00:48:59.305
to give up all the other
cherished notions of Newtonian

00:48:59.305 --> 00:49:02.059
physics.
Think about why.

00:49:02.059 --> 00:49:05.758
We are saying,
here is a car going at 200

00:49:05.758 --> 00:49:08.809
miles an hour,
according to me.

00:49:08.809 --> 00:49:12.519
You get into your own car and
follow that car at 50 miles an

00:49:12.519 --> 00:49:15.693
hour.
You should get 150 but you keep

00:49:15.693 --> 00:49:18.445
getting 200.
This may not be true for cars

00:49:18.445 --> 00:49:21.934
going at the speeds I mentioned
but when finally you are talking

00:49:21.934 --> 00:49:24.150
about a pulse of light,
that is true.

00:49:24.150 --> 00:49:28.205
And you've got to agree that is
really not compatible with our

00:49:28.205 --> 00:49:31.263
daily notions or with the
formula I wrote down,

00:49:31.263 --> 00:49:34.450
w = v - u.
When you put v = c,

00:49:34.450 --> 00:49:37.550
w has got to come out to
be c.

00:49:37.550 --> 00:49:40.650
And that's not a property of
the Newtonian transformation.

00:49:40.650 --> 00:49:44.528
So, what we are looking for is
a new rule for connecting

00:49:44.528 --> 00:49:48.194
x and t and
x prime and t

00:49:48.194 --> 00:49:50.919
prime,
such that when the velocities

00:49:50.919 --> 00:49:54.470
are computed and applied to the
velocity of light,

00:49:54.470 --> 00:49:57.949
you get the same answer.
That's what we want to do now.

00:49:57.949 --> 00:50:01.010
So, here is how we are going to
do this.

00:50:01.010 --> 00:50:04.914
Now, let's think about it.
Let me send a pulse to the

00:50:04.914 --> 00:50:08.895
right at speed c.
You are going to the right at

00:50:08.895 --> 00:50:12.884
three-fourths of c.
My Newtonian expectation is,

00:50:12.884 --> 00:50:16.232
you should get the speed of the
pulse to be one-fourth of

00:50:16.232 --> 00:50:19.020
c.
But you insist it is c.

00:50:19.020 --> 00:50:22.349
So, what will I say to you?
What will I accuse you of doing?

00:50:22.349 --> 00:50:26.389
I say you should get c/4
and you're getting c.

00:50:26.389 --> 00:50:29.874
And you're finding velocity by
finding the distance it travels

00:50:29.874 --> 00:50:33.243
and dividing by the time so you
are jacking up a number like

00:50:33.243 --> 00:50:35.700
one-fourth c to c
itself.

00:50:35.700 --> 00:50:39.510
So, what could make you do that?
Yep?

00:50:39.510 --> 00:50:43.235
Student: If I perceive
that you're moving forward,

00:50:43.235 --> 00:50:45.630
or you're contracting your
length,

00:50:45.630 --> 00:50:51.213
then you're going to measure
velocity keeping in mind you

00:50:51.213 --> 00:50:56.099
should have had a greater length
to begin with.

00:50:56.099 --> 00:50:56.650
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Yes.

00:50:56.650 --> 00:50:58.929
So, one option--Let me repeat
what he said.

00:50:58.929 --> 00:51:03.610
I will say your meter sticks
are being somehow shorter.

00:51:03.610 --> 00:51:06.329
When you and I were buddies and
were on the same train,

00:51:06.329 --> 00:51:08.956
we agreed on the meter stick.
But now we have gone on the

00:51:08.956 --> 00:51:11.065
moving train.
I will say there is something

00:51:11.065 --> 00:51:13.690
wrong with your meter stick.
Not only something wrong.

00:51:13.690 --> 00:51:15.182
Specifically,
I would say your meter sticks

00:51:15.182 --> 00:51:16.262
have shrunk.
For example,

00:51:16.262 --> 00:51:18.396
if they have shrunk to
one-fourth their size,

00:51:18.396 --> 00:51:21.258
it is very clear that you would
get a velocity of four times

00:51:21.258 --> 00:51:25.679
what I expect.
But there's another possibility.

00:51:25.679 --> 00:51:27.829
Student: Time may be
running slow.

00:51:27.829 --> 00:51:29.170
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Your clocks may be

00:51:29.170 --> 00:51:30.828
running slow.
So, you let the light travel

00:51:30.828 --> 00:51:33.429
for four seconds and you thought
it was only one second.

00:51:33.429 --> 00:51:35.320
That's why you got four times
the answer;

00:51:35.320 --> 00:51:38.820
or it could be both.
But something has to give.

00:51:38.820 --> 00:51:43.050
And that is why it is an
amazing theory.

00:51:43.050 --> 00:51:46.839
That's why it is also amazing
to me that somebody who was 26

00:51:46.839 --> 00:51:50.628
years old would simply follow
the consequence of this theory

00:51:50.628 --> 00:51:54.096
and take it wherever it takes
you but it is at the very

00:51:54.096 --> 00:51:57.949
foundations of space and time
that you have to modify.

00:51:57.949 --> 00:52:00.447
So, even though you restored
the relativity principle and

00:52:00.447 --> 00:52:03.582
brought it back to the front,
the price you have to pay is to

00:52:03.582 --> 00:52:07.030
give up your notions that length
is length and time is time.

00:52:07.030 --> 00:52:09.452
We used to think a meter stick
is a meter stick and a clock is

00:52:09.452 --> 00:52:11.317
a clock.
If I have a clock that ticks

00:52:11.317 --> 00:52:13.308
out one second,
you take it on a train,

00:52:13.308 --> 00:52:16.348
I expect it to be ticking one
second, but we're saying it's

00:52:16.348 --> 00:52:18.695
not.
So, something has to give in

00:52:18.695 --> 00:52:21.909
length measurement or time
measurement or both.

00:52:21.909 --> 00:52:24.449
And that's what we're going to
find out.

00:52:24.449 --> 00:52:26.659
So, here's how you find that
out.

00:52:26.659 --> 00:52:33.314
Let us say that--Maybe I'll do
it all on one blackboard because

00:52:33.314 --> 00:52:37.929
this is the key to the whole
calculation.

00:52:37.929 --> 00:52:42.379
You remember now,
if there is an event here,

00:52:42.379 --> 00:52:47.760
you call it x prime and
I call it x.

00:52:51.539 --> 00:52:53.588
And according to me,
you have traveled the distance

00:52:53.588 --> 00:52:54.080
ut.

00:52:59.909 --> 00:53:08.812
So, x prime equals x
- ut is what we used to say

00:53:08.812 --> 00:53:14.940
in the old days.
And the converse of that is

00:53:14.940 --> 00:53:20.272
x = x prime + ut.
But now, we'll admit the fact

00:53:20.272 --> 00:53:22.840
that maybe t and t
prime are no longer the same.

00:53:26.660 --> 00:53:31.015
But that's not all we will do.
I will say, whenever you give

00:53:31.015 --> 00:53:34.099
me a length x prime,
I just don't buy it.

00:53:34.099 --> 00:53:39.020
I take any length you give me
and I jack it up by a factor of

00:53:39.020 --> 00:53:43.203
γ [correction:
should have said 1/γ]

00:53:43.203 --> 00:53:46.320
to get the length according to
me.

00:53:46.320 --> 00:53:50.191
And you will take any answer I
give you and you will multiply

00:53:50.191 --> 00:53:53.840
it by the same factor.
Don't worry about this yet!]

00:53:53.840 --> 00:53:56.840
In other words,
we don't buy our units of

00:53:56.840 --> 00:53:59.473
length,
so if you say it should be

00:53:59.473 --> 00:54:03.241
x prime + ut
prime, that's your formula

00:54:03.241 --> 00:54:06.072
backwards for me.
The coordinate of the event,

00:54:06.072 --> 00:54:07.701
according to you,
in the old days,

00:54:07.701 --> 00:54:10.869
was x prime + ut.
Now, we admit that t and

00:54:10.869 --> 00:54:12.599
t prime may not be the
same.

00:54:12.599 --> 00:54:14.964
Then we say,
but I will not take your

00:54:14.964 --> 00:54:18.906
lengths, I will multiply them by
γ to get the lengths

00:54:18.906 --> 00:54:21.542
according to me.
And you will not take my

00:54:21.542 --> 00:54:23.967
expectations,
but you will multiply it by the

00:54:23.967 --> 00:54:27.045
same γ;
that is the symmetry between

00:54:27.045 --> 00:54:29.015
the two observers.
In other words,

00:54:29.015 --> 00:54:30.905
if I think your meter sticks
are short and γ

00:54:30.905 --> 00:54:32.425
[correction: should have said
1/γ]

00:54:32.425 --> 00:54:35.122
is a number less than 1,
I'm allowing you to accuse me

00:54:35.122 --> 00:54:37.360
of having meter sticks which are
short.

00:54:37.360 --> 00:54:40.133
It is very interesting.
If I said your meter sticks are

00:54:40.133 --> 00:54:43.082
short and you say my meter
sticks are longer than average,

00:54:43.082 --> 00:54:46.434
that's an absolute difference.
But we both accuse each other

00:54:46.434 --> 00:54:49.892
of using shortened meter sticks,
and so we use the same factor

00:54:49.892 --> 00:54:53.025
of γ.
We are going to find this

00:54:53.025 --> 00:54:56.796
γ now.
Student: How do you know

00:54:56.796 --> 00:55:00.489
that both the distance and time
are different?

00:55:00.489 --> 00:55:03.151
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: We'll give it the

00:55:03.151 --> 00:55:05.966
possibility that they are
different and then we will see

00:55:05.966 --> 00:55:08.530
that they are different.
We know something's wrong with

00:55:08.530 --> 00:55:10.000
space and something's wrong with
time.

00:55:10.000 --> 00:55:12.155
So, we'll not assume that
t prime is equal to

00:55:12.155 --> 00:55:13.731
t.
You have to open up the

00:55:13.731 --> 00:55:15.969
possibility.
In the end, it may be that the

00:55:15.969 --> 00:55:18.921
nature will say t prime
is t and something

00:55:18.921 --> 00:55:22.018
happens to length alone.
But we'll find the answer is

00:55:22.018 --> 00:55:27.131
more symmetric.
Student: Why do we say

00:55:27.131 --> 00:55:32.373
that the symmetry is the same?
Professor Ramamurti

00:55:32.373 --> 00:55:34.367
Shankar: Because that is the
symmetry between the two

00:55:34.367 --> 00:55:37.427
observers.
If I want to say your meter

00:55:37.427 --> 00:55:41.949
sticks are short,
why should you concede that?

00:55:41.949 --> 00:55:43.976
You should be able to accuse me
of saying--The only difference

00:55:43.976 --> 00:55:45.836
between you and me is you are
moving to the right and I'm

00:55:45.836 --> 00:55:48.109
moving to the left.
Other than the sign of the

00:55:48.109 --> 00:55:51.708
velocity, each person says the
other person is moving and so we

00:55:51.708 --> 00:55:55.075
will say that any length you
give I'll discount by a factor

00:55:55.075 --> 00:55:56.644
of γ.
By symmetry,

00:55:56.644 --> 00:55:59.004
anything I call a length,
you will discount by the same

00:55:59.004 --> 00:56:02.639
factor of γ.
Now, let's apply this.

00:56:02.639 --> 00:56:04.390
(x,t) was a
certain event,

00:56:04.390 --> 00:56:06.479
right?
Let's apply it to the following

00:56:06.479 --> 00:56:07.975
event.
You have to follow this very

00:56:07.975 --> 00:56:10.014
carefully.
When you and I crossed,

00:56:10.014 --> 00:56:13.224
remember that was at the origin
of coordinates,

00:56:13.224 --> 00:56:16.991
x equals to t
equals to zero and x

00:56:16.991 --> 00:56:20.550
prime equals to t prime
equals to zero.

00:56:20.550 --> 00:56:23.231
At that instant when our
origins touched,

00:56:23.231 --> 00:56:27.407
let us emit a flash of light.
Okay, maybe when the origins

00:56:27.407 --> 00:56:31.454
touched, there's a spark,
the light signal goes out and

00:56:31.454 --> 00:56:35.800
the light signal is detected
here, by a light detector.

00:56:35.800 --> 00:56:41.765
That second event,
detection of the pulse,

00:56:41.765 --> 00:56:49.039
it has a coordinates
(x,t) for me;

00:56:49.039 --> 00:56:54.429
it has a coordinates (x
prime, t prime) for you.

00:56:54.429 --> 00:56:58.050
The same event is given
different coordinates.

00:56:58.050 --> 00:57:00.365
We've already used the fact
that coordinates will be

00:57:00.365 --> 00:57:03.181
different but we are saying not
only will x prime not be

00:57:03.181 --> 00:57:05.316
equal to x;
t prime may not be equal

00:57:05.316 --> 00:57:06.050
to t either.

00:57:10.650 --> 00:57:15.360
Okay, but now let's write down
one important condition.

00:57:15.360 --> 00:57:17.542
What is the relation between
x prime and t

00:57:17.542 --> 00:57:19.210
prime in this particular pair of
events?

00:57:24.430 --> 00:57:27.314
What is x prime?
It is the location of the light

00:57:27.314 --> 00:57:30.820
pulse after certain time?
So, what's the relation of the

00:57:30.820 --> 00:57:34.460
location of the detection of the
light pulse and the time

00:57:34.460 --> 00:57:39.690
t prime?
Yes?

00:57:39.690 --> 00:57:43.496
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

00:57:43.496 --> 00:57:47.536
Shankar: He is saying
x prime--Do you guys

00:57:47.536 --> 00:57:50.223
understand that?
Do you agree with that

00:57:50.223 --> 00:57:52.429
statement?
This is not a random event.

00:57:52.429 --> 00:57:55.659
The second event was the
detection of a light pulse.

00:57:55.659 --> 00:57:59.272
Light pulse left the origin
t prime seconds earlier

00:57:59.272 --> 00:58:02.337
and has come to this point,
according to this guy,

00:58:02.337 --> 00:58:05.628
and the ratio of the distance
to the time is the velocity of

00:58:05.628 --> 00:58:08.306
light.
But it is also true that for

00:58:08.306 --> 00:58:12.969
me, the light went to distance
x in a time t.

00:58:12.969 --> 00:58:17.377
So, that's the relation of
x to t for me

00:58:17.377 --> 00:58:20.427
also.
I'm going to use those two

00:58:20.427 --> 00:58:26.217
results and combine it with this
to find this factor γ

00:58:26.217 --> 00:58:30.593
and we will do that now.
I want you to multiply the

00:58:30.593 --> 00:58:34.919
left-hand side by the left-hand
side and the right-hand side by

00:58:34.919 --> 00:58:37.710
the right-hand side of that
equation.

00:58:37.710 --> 00:58:41.050
I hope you understand that in
the Galilean days,

00:58:41.050 --> 00:58:44.389
in the old days--Let's see what
you will say.

00:58:44.389 --> 00:58:46.841
I will say, x prime is
x - ut because the

00:58:46.841 --> 00:58:48.929
origins have shifted by an
amount ut.

00:58:48.929 --> 00:58:51.853
And you will say x is
x prime plus ut

00:58:51.853 --> 00:58:53.985
with the same time.
Now, I'm saying time is

00:58:53.985 --> 00:58:55.261
different.
Not only that,

00:58:55.261 --> 00:58:58.575
I don't buy your length.
If you expect me to have this

00:58:58.575 --> 00:59:01.210
length, I say "no."
You exaggerated everything.

00:59:01.210 --> 00:59:03.969
I'll scale it down by γ
and vice versa.

00:59:03.969 --> 00:59:07.115
So, if you multiply the
left-hand side by the left-hand

00:59:07.115 --> 00:59:11.726
side, you get xx prime,
the right-hand side you get

00:59:11.726 --> 00:59:17.424
γ^(2) times xx
prime plus uxt prime

00:59:17.424 --> 00:59:23.630
minus ux prime t
minus u^(2)tt prime.

00:59:30.769 --> 00:59:35.630
Now, divide everything by
xx prime.

00:59:35.630 --> 00:59:41.300
Then, you get 1 = γ^(2)
times 1 + u.

00:59:41.300 --> 00:59:44.338
If you divide this by xx
prime, you'll get t prime

00:59:44.338 --> 00:59:48.250
over x prime.
If you divide this by xx

00:59:48.250 --> 00:59:52.903
prime, you'll get t/x.
And here you get u^(2)

00:59:52.903 --> 00:59:55.644
times t/x,
times t prime over

00:59:55.644 --> 00:59:56.820
x prime.

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:10.824
So, what does that mean?
Well, t prime over

01:00:10.824 --> 01:00:15.324
x prime is 1/c and
t/x is also

01:00:15.324 --> 01:00:18.719
1/c because of what I
wrote here.

01:00:18.719 --> 01:00:20.733
If you want,
let me write this as t

01:00:20.733 --> 01:00:23.779
prime over x prime equals
the c and t over

01:00:23.779 --> 01:00:26.969
x equals the c.
So, they will cancel.

01:00:26.969 --> 01:00:31.569
And I'll get 1 = γ^(2)
times 1 - u^(2) over

01:00:31.569 --> 01:00:36.007
c^(2) because this
t/x is a 1/c and

01:00:36.007 --> 01:00:40.930
t prime over x
prime is another 1/c.

01:00:44.949 --> 01:00:50.776
So, that gives us the result
that γ is 1 over square

01:00:50.776 --> 01:00:55.220
root of 1 - u^(2) over
c^(2).

01:01:00.889 --> 01:01:05.660
If you plug the γ back
in, you will find x prime

01:01:05.660 --> 01:01:08.969
is x - ut divided by
[square root of]

01:01:08.969 --> 01:01:11.970
1 - u^(2) over
c^(2).

01:01:22.320 --> 01:01:24.758
Now, once you do that,
once you got the relation

01:01:24.758 --> 01:01:27.509
between x prime and
x, you can go to the

01:01:27.509 --> 01:01:30.000
lower equation and solve for
t prime.

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:33.698
I don't feel like doing that.
It's a simple algebraic

01:01:33.698 --> 01:01:36.517
equation once you've got
x prime how to solve for

01:01:36.517 --> 01:01:38.645
t prime.
Take the second of the two

01:01:38.645 --> 01:01:40.500
equations and solve for t
prime.

01:01:40.500 --> 01:01:45.326
That detail I won't fill out,
but you will get t prime

01:01:45.326 --> 01:01:49.590
is t - ux over
c^(2) divided by this.

01:01:49.590 --> 01:01:52.889
So, I've not done every step
but I've given you all the

01:01:52.889 --> 01:01:55.150
things you need to do the one
step.

01:01:55.150 --> 01:01:57.650
There are equations up there
that relate x and

01:01:57.650 --> 01:02:00.631
x prime to t and
t prime so if you can get

01:02:00.631 --> 01:02:03.179
x prime in terms of
x and t,

01:02:03.179 --> 01:02:05.414
the other equation that you
solve will give you t

01:02:05.414 --> 01:02:07.120
prime in terms of x and
t.

01:02:07.120 --> 01:02:08.540
And this is the result.

01:02:12.420 --> 01:02:15.952
Okay.
This guy deserves two boxes

01:02:15.952 --> 01:02:21.000
because it is the greatest
result from relativity;

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:23.440
it's called the Lorentz
transformation.

01:02:23.440 --> 01:02:28.474
And we've been able to derive
the Lorentz transformation with

01:02:28.474 --> 01:02:30.953
what little we know.
And you can see,

01:02:30.953 --> 01:02:33.050
you can be a kid in high school
and you can do this.

01:02:33.050 --> 01:02:35.951
There's no calculus or anything
else involved,

01:02:35.951 --> 01:02:39.756
other than being open to the
fact that the velocity of light

01:02:39.756 --> 01:02:44.309
behaves in this strange way.
Yes?

01:02:44.309 --> 01:02:48.329
Student: How do you get
t/x = c?

01:02:48.329 --> 01:02:49.666
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Why is t/x =

01:02:49.666 --> 01:02:51.489
c?
Oh, of course,

01:02:51.489 --> 01:02:56.719
you're quite right.
So, you caught the mistake here.

01:02:56.719 --> 01:03:00.590
t/x is 1 over c
and 1/c.

01:03:00.590 --> 01:03:02.960
I really meant to write x =
ct.

01:03:02.960 --> 01:03:05.963
Yes?
Student: [inaudible]

01:03:05.963 --> 01:03:09.449
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No.

01:03:09.449 --> 01:03:13.810
If you define γ to be
the absolute value by which you

01:03:13.810 --> 01:03:18.315
transfer lengths from you to me,
then you can take the positive

01:03:18.315 --> 01:03:19.663
root.
Student: [inaudible]

01:03:19.663 --> 01:03:20.690
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Well,

01:03:20.690 --> 01:03:21.640
I can also tell you other
reasons.

01:03:21.640 --> 01:03:26.926
Let's take this formula here.
Let's take the case where the

01:03:26.926 --> 01:03:30.659
velocity is very small compared
to the velocity of light.

01:03:30.659 --> 01:03:33.110
That u/c is a very small
number.

01:03:33.110 --> 01:03:36.751
This number is almost 1 and I
get x prime because x

01:03:36.751 --> 01:03:40.089
- ut, which I know to be the
correct answer at lower

01:03:40.089 --> 01:03:42.753
velocities.
If you pick the minus sign,

01:03:42.753 --> 01:03:46.131
I'll get minus of x -
ut, that's not the right

01:03:46.131 --> 01:03:49.119
answer, not even close to the
right answer.

01:03:49.119 --> 01:03:52.608
At low velocities,
if you go to velocity u

01:03:52.608 --> 01:03:56.824
over c much less than 1,
you have got to get back to

01:03:56.824 --> 01:04:00.507
Galilean transformation.
You can see if u over

01:04:00.507 --> 01:04:03.703
c goes to zero.
You can forget all about this

01:04:03.703 --> 01:04:05.823
factor here.
You get x prime is

01:04:05.823 --> 01:04:08.877
x - ut and here,
u over c can be

01:04:08.877 --> 01:04:10.632
neglected,
forget all that,

01:04:10.632 --> 01:04:13.340
you get t prime equals
t.

01:04:13.340 --> 01:04:17.313
So, this coordinate
transformation would reduce to

01:04:17.313 --> 01:04:22.259
the Galilean transformation if
the velocity between me and you

01:04:22.259 --> 01:04:26.070
is much smaller than the
velocity of light.

01:04:26.070 --> 01:04:30.267
So, the formula really kicks in
for velocities comparable to

01:04:30.267 --> 01:04:35.820
velocity of light.
Yes?

01:04:35.820 --> 01:04:38.081
Student: [inaudible]
What happens if u &gt;

01:04:38.081 --> 01:04:39.114
c?
Professor Ramamurti

01:04:39.114 --> 01:04:40.389
Shankar: Well,
you start getting crazy

01:04:40.389 --> 01:04:42.807
answers, right?
You can already see that the

01:04:42.807 --> 01:04:46.722
theory will not admit velocities
bigger than the velocity of

01:04:46.722 --> 01:04:48.681
light.
You can already see it in this

01:04:48.681 --> 01:04:50.819
formula.
That tells you that the one

01:04:50.819 --> 01:04:54.791
single velocity that you wanted
to be the same for everybody is

01:04:54.791 --> 01:04:57.289
also the greatest possible
velocity;

01:04:57.289 --> 01:05:00.804
that no observer can move at
this speed with respect to

01:05:00.804 --> 01:05:04.513
another observer that is equal
to what is in excess of the

01:05:04.513 --> 01:05:06.913
speed of light.
So, the speed of light,

01:05:06.913 --> 01:05:10.150
which came out to be a constant
in the beginning of the theory,

01:05:10.150 --> 01:05:13.213
is also turning out to be the
upper limit on possible

01:05:13.213 --> 01:05:15.525
velocities.
That's the origin of the

01:05:15.525 --> 01:05:19.323
statement that no observer can
travel at a speed bigger than

01:05:19.323 --> 01:05:22.219
light, but we'll discuss it more
and more.

01:05:22.219 --> 01:05:26.743
But you have to understand what
it is that is being derived,

01:05:26.743 --> 01:05:30.040
what is the meaning of this
formula here.

01:05:30.040 --> 01:05:33.007
What is it telling you?
If I say, this is called the

01:05:33.007 --> 01:05:36.460
Lorenz transformations,
what do they tell you?

01:05:36.460 --> 01:05:40.820
What are these numbers and
what's their significance?

01:05:40.820 --> 01:05:44.122
Would you like to try?
Student: Well,

01:05:44.122 --> 01:05:47.197
one thing that they tell you is
if u happens to be

01:05:47.197 --> 01:05:48.954
greater than c
[inaudible]

01:05:48.954 --> 01:05:51.369
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No,

01:05:51.369 --> 01:05:54.580
no, I don't mean what happens
in the formula in special cases.

01:05:54.580 --> 01:05:57.569
What is it relating?
What is xt and what is

01:05:57.569 --> 01:06:00.995
x prime t prime?
Student:

01:06:00.995 --> 01:06:07.216
Okay, so x prime would
be the distance that the person

01:06:07.216 --> 01:06:12.089
who's traveling at the higher
speed experiences.

01:06:12.089 --> 01:06:16.029
And [inaudible]
and so for that person,

01:06:16.029 --> 01:06:20.280
distance is going to seem
shorter?

01:06:20.280 --> 01:06:22.340
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No.

01:06:22.340 --> 01:06:25.123
See, I'm not even telling you
to get consequences of the

01:06:25.123 --> 01:06:27.700
equation.
What are the numbers x

01:06:27.700 --> 01:06:30.829
and t in this equation?
And what are the numbers

01:06:30.829 --> 01:06:32.929
x prime and t
prime in this equation?

01:06:32.929 --> 01:06:36.723
Student: x and
t are distance and time

01:06:36.723 --> 01:06:40.190
for a person who is in an
inertial frame of reference,

01:06:40.190 --> 01:06:42.038
who is not moving.
Professor Ramamurti

01:06:42.038 --> 01:06:43.535
Shankar: Right.
Student: And x

01:06:43.535 --> 01:06:45.947
prime and t prime are
distance and time for the person

01:06:45.947 --> 01:06:47.555
who is moving at the speed of
[inaudible]

01:06:47.555 --> 01:06:49.605
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: And when you say

01:06:49.605 --> 01:06:51.615
distance and time,
what do you mean,

01:06:51.615 --> 01:06:54.549
distance and time?
Student: The way that

01:06:54.549 --> 01:06:58.619
the length of the distance will
seem to them that they travel.

01:06:58.619 --> 01:06:59.876
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: But what is

01:06:59.876 --> 01:07:03.159
happening at xt;
it's the coordinates of what?

01:07:03.159 --> 01:07:04.920
Student: Of their
location [inaudible]

01:07:04.920 --> 01:07:07.079
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: They are located at

01:07:07.079 --> 01:07:09.190
zero, zero.
Right?

01:07:09.190 --> 01:07:10.500
What's happening at x
and t?

01:07:10.500 --> 01:07:15.303
Yes?
Student: It's observing

01:07:15.303 --> 01:07:17.092
the event.
Professor Ramamurti

01:07:17.092 --> 01:07:19.308
Shankar: It's the event.
The key I was looking for is an

01:07:19.308 --> 01:07:21.248
event.
You've got to understand what

01:07:21.248 --> 01:07:25.218
the formula is connecting.
Things are happening in space

01:07:25.218 --> 01:07:28.659
and in time, right?
Something happens here.

01:07:28.659 --> 01:07:31.997
That something has a spatial
coordinate and a time

01:07:31.997 --> 01:07:34.789
coordinate, according to two
observers.

01:07:34.789 --> 01:07:38.263
The observers originally had
their origins and their clocks

01:07:38.263 --> 01:07:41.510
coincide when they passed;
that's how they're related.

01:07:41.510 --> 01:07:43.880
And one is moving to the right
at speed u.

01:07:43.880 --> 01:07:47.848
Then, the claim is that if one
event had a coordinate x

01:07:47.848 --> 01:07:51.235
and t for one person,
for the other person moving to

01:07:51.235 --> 01:07:53.772
the right at speed u,
the same event would have

01:07:53.772 --> 01:07:56.692
coordinates x prime and
t prime and the relation

01:07:56.692 --> 01:07:59.564
between x and t
and x prime and t

01:07:59.564 --> 01:08:03.530
prime is this.
Yes?

01:08:03.530 --> 01:08:07.815
Student: The two
observers [inaudible]

01:08:07.815 --> 01:08:12.491
don't they observe different
laws and [inaudible]

01:08:12.491 --> 01:08:16.680
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: No.

01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:19.792
The fact that an event has
different coordinates doesn't

01:08:19.792 --> 01:08:22.340
mean that you are observing
different laws.

01:08:22.340 --> 01:08:24.927
For example,
let's take that fire

01:08:24.927 --> 01:08:27.194
extinguisher.
We look at it,

01:08:27.194 --> 01:08:29.829
it's obeying F = ma,
right?

01:08:29.829 --> 01:08:32.591
The coordinates of the fire
extinguisher with me as the

01:08:32.591 --> 01:08:35.199
origin is quite different from
you as the origin.

01:08:35.199 --> 01:08:44.224
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

01:08:44.224 --> 01:08:52.880
Shankar: You mean in these
new equations?

01:08:52.880 --> 01:08:55.940
Yes, in these new equations,
F = ma will not work;

01:08:55.940 --> 01:08:58.540
that's correct.
Student: They are

01:08:58.540 --> 01:09:00.479
inertial references,
even though they are moving?

01:09:00.479 --> 01:09:01.310
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Ah.

01:09:01.310 --> 01:09:04.294
Yes.
So, the point is the laws of

01:09:04.294 --> 01:09:07.350
Newton themselves have to be
modified.

01:09:07.350 --> 01:09:11.702
F = ma will be modified
in a certain way but the new

01:09:11.702 --> 01:09:16.430
modified laws will reduce to
F = ma at low velocities,

01:09:16.430 --> 01:09:19.529
which is why in the old days it
looked like F = ma.

01:09:19.529 --> 01:09:22.607
But there will be new laws,
but they will also have the

01:09:22.607 --> 01:09:26.026
property that when I measure
them I'll get the laws that will

01:09:26.026 --> 01:09:29.239
agree with what you measure.
Yes?

01:09:29.239 --> 01:09:34.430
Student: Does individual
values for time or distance

01:09:34.430 --> 01:09:37.221
still have to agree?
Professor Ramamurti

01:09:37.221 --> 01:09:39.574
Shankar: The coordinates of
an event will differ from person

01:09:39.574 --> 01:09:42.038
to person.
That's not the same as saying

01:09:42.038 --> 01:09:44.699
the laws as deduced will be
different.

01:09:44.699 --> 01:09:46.490
For example,
there are two stars which are

01:09:46.490 --> 01:09:48.673
attracted to each other by
gravitation and they are

01:09:48.673 --> 01:09:50.770
orbiting around their common
center of mass.

01:09:50.770 --> 01:09:52.626
If I see them,
I will find that they obey the

01:09:52.626 --> 01:09:54.313
law of gravitation with
m_1m

01:09:54.313 --> 01:09:56.464
_2 over
r^(2) where r is

01:09:56.464 --> 01:09:59.122
the distance between the points
and the acceleration is whatever

01:09:59.122 --> 01:10:01.783
I think it is.
You can go on a rocket and look

01:10:01.783 --> 01:10:04.227
at the same two stars.
They will be in a more

01:10:04.227 --> 01:10:06.806
complicated motion,
maybe the whole system will be

01:10:06.806 --> 01:10:09.866
drifting a little to you,
but their acceleration will be

01:10:09.866 --> 01:10:13.091
the same as what I get and the
force between them will also be

01:10:13.091 --> 01:10:16.211
the same as what I get and the
laws that you would deduce by

01:10:16.211 --> 01:10:19.119
looking at that star would be
the same laws that I would

01:10:19.119 --> 01:10:21.641
deduce.
So, that's a difference between

01:10:21.641 --> 01:10:25.090
the laws being the same and the
coordinates being the same.

01:10:25.090 --> 01:10:28.071
No one said x prime and
x are the same in that

01:10:28.071 --> 01:10:29.909
equation there.
They are different.

01:10:29.909 --> 01:10:31.600
We are looking at it from
different vantage points.

01:10:31.600 --> 01:10:36.376
But the fact is that force is
equal to mass times acceleration

01:10:36.376 --> 01:10:41.489
is the same for the two people.
Okay.

01:10:41.489 --> 01:10:44.000
The laws will be the same but
things won't look the same.

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:45.861
For example,
you can stand on your head,

01:10:45.861 --> 01:10:48.439
don't even have to go to
another frame of reference;

01:10:48.439 --> 01:10:50.514
you can stand on your head,
your z coordinate is the

01:10:50.514 --> 01:10:52.713
minus of my z coordinate;
to every point I give a

01:10:52.713 --> 01:10:54.510
z, you will give a minus
z.

01:10:54.510 --> 01:10:56.580
But the world,
even though you are a little

01:10:56.580 --> 01:10:58.699
messed up and want to stand on
your head,

01:10:58.699 --> 01:11:01.752
you have every right to do that
and you will find that F =

01:11:01.752 --> 01:11:03.513
ma.
So the point is,

01:11:03.513 --> 01:11:07.587
the way we see events may
depend on their origin or

01:11:07.587 --> 01:11:10.452
coordinates,
but the laws we deduce are to

01:11:10.452 --> 01:11:13.340
be distinguished from the
perception that we have.

01:11:13.340 --> 01:11:15.472
Okay?
For example,

01:11:15.472 --> 01:11:18.070
if I'm on the ground,
I send a piece of chalk,

01:11:18.070 --> 01:11:21.025
it goes up and it goes down.
If you see me from a moving

01:11:21.025 --> 01:11:23.010
train, you would think it went
on a parabola.

01:11:23.010 --> 01:11:25.970
So, no one says the chalk will
go up and down for you.

01:11:25.970 --> 01:11:30.478
For you, it will go like this
but its motion will still obey

01:11:30.478 --> 01:11:33.229
F = ma,
is what I'm saying.

01:11:33.229 --> 01:11:37.090
That's all you really mean by
saying things look the same.

01:11:37.090 --> 01:11:41.324
So, what you have to understand
is that Lorentz transformations

01:11:41.324 --> 01:11:45.080
are the way to relate a pair of
events, given events.

01:11:45.080 --> 01:11:47.928
Here's a simple example.
If you live in the xy

01:11:47.928 --> 01:11:50.234
plane, there's a point here.
It's not an event,

01:11:50.234 --> 01:11:52.079
it's simply a point in the
xy plane.

01:11:52.079 --> 01:11:54.885
You measure it this way and
that way and you call it the

01:11:54.885 --> 01:11:57.345
coordinates.
If somebody else picks a

01:11:57.345 --> 01:12:01.199
different coordinate system with
an angle θ,

01:12:01.199 --> 01:12:04.439
that person will say that's
x prime and that is

01:12:04.439 --> 01:12:08.045
y prime and x
prime and y prime are not

01:12:08.045 --> 01:12:09.575
the same.
I remind you,

01:12:09.575 --> 01:12:12.460
x prime is x cos&gt;
θ [delete "minus

01:12:12.460 --> 01:12:14.214
y"]
plus y sin θ,

01:12:14.214 --> 01:12:16.930
etc., and y prime is
something else.

01:12:16.930 --> 01:12:19.720
θ is the angle between
the two observers.

01:12:19.720 --> 01:12:23.031
So, the point is the point.
It certainly looks different to

